task.summary: Default task
A moderately massive commit, which defines business logic of the server. That includes: - Implementation of Stratago - Chat - Rooms - Server Events
- Now rooms will delete themselves when empty they are empty, unless they were just created - BackendApi will now verify time controls proposed by a user

- Now rooms will delete themselves when empty they are empty, unless they were just created - BackendApi will now verify time controls proposed by a user - Added a field signature in EventLogicalEndpoint to allow shared endpoints - EventLogicalEndpoints can now be merged in order to reduce amount of events being delivered
- Finished a runnable version of the backend server - Organized some src files
- Created a primitive interface between websockets clients and our Backend Nodes Api. - Added a few unit test
- small bugfixes
- Now rooms will close themselves after 10 minutes of inactivity.
Starting the room termination countdown
- Added a websocket service on port 5001 - A few bugfixes
- Now threads support signals such as sigint and sigterm
- Started work on UI, now on /board server would generate a board, that is for now, empty

- Allowed browser user to create and join rooms. Thought, there is no button to set_ready value yet, so users would be stuck in awaiting phase. - Seat placement and chat features are integrated into browser client
Reworked window visible in awaiting phase
First playable version, introduced controller for board in gameplay phase. A number of bugfixes
- Added index.html - Fixed small bug regarding the loading of user's username in board.html
- Added a few testCases and comments
- Even more testcases
- Even more tests
- Even more tests for table.py
- Refactored game representation from stratego.py into stratego_gamestate.py, while leaving game login in stratego.py. - Added a position parser in test utils to load test positions.
- Added a few testing positions, ready to work on mov generator rework

- Added support for move generation from C++ dll - Added a factory to create game instances - Factory now has a method called "create_default" which would return new c backed game instance if this is possible, or old python implementation if the former is not available
- Added clocks to show players remaining time
- Now setting passwords for the room works correctly
- Fixed bug in dll, now winner piece gets discovered
- Fixed bug in dll, now winner piece gets discovered
